uk.ac.ebi.pride.jmztab.model

Class Metadata

  • java.lang.Object
    • uk.ac.ebi.pride.jmztab.model.Metadata

  • public class Metadata
extends Object
    The metadata section can provide additional information about the dataset(s) reported in the mzTab file. All fields in the metadata section are optional apart from five exceptions: - "mzTab-version" MUST always be reported. - "mzTab-mode" MUST always be reported. Two modes are possible: 'Summary' and 'Complete'. - "mzTab-type" MUST always be reported. Two types are possible: 'Quantification' or 'Identification'. Any analyses generating both quantification and identification results MUST be flagged as 'Quantification'. - "description" MUST always be reported. - "ms_run-location[1-n]" MUST always be reported.
    Since:
    23/05/13
    Author:
    qingwei

The output line structure like: MTD item[map.key] map.value For example: MTD sample_processing[1] [SEP, SEP:00173, SDS PAGE, ] MTD sample_processing[2] [SEP, SEP:00142, enzyme digestion, ]|[MS, MS:1001251, Trypsin, ]
